{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a482c10a-2153-47f2-9444-c7836dba3a2a","content":"## Summary of Changes\n\n| File | Change | Reason |\n|------|--------|--------|\n| `global.json` | `9.0.100` + `rollForward: latestFeature` | Targets .NET 9 SDK; allows patch flexibility |\n| `MultiTarget.csproj` | `net7.0` → `net9.0`, `netstandard1.6` → `netstandard2.0` | net7.0 is EOL; netstandard1.6 has very limited API surface |\n| `ci-build.sh` | Added `set -e`; used `--machine-readable` for workload list | Fail on build errors; .NET 9 changed workload list output format |\n\n## ⚠️ Team Blocker: Visual Studio Version\n\n**VS 2022 17.11 does NOT support .NET 9 projects.** Your team must upgrade to **VS 2022 17.12 or later**. Without this, developers will get project load errors and IntelliSense failures for `net9.0` targets.\n\n## `dotnet watch` for local dev\n\nWith multiple TFMs, developers should now run:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch --framework net8.0\n```\n\nThis explicitly selects the `net8.0` TFM for the inner-loop, avoiding ambiguity in .NET 9's updated `dotnet watch` behavior.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f53c5cda-aad3-4f58-bd1c-09def12d8908","outputTokens":330,"requestId":"9838:B7F6F:2540E8:2E667A:69F553A3"},"id":"6880303d-e305-4256-95c2-61cf2548d6d7","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:30:21.078Z","parentId":"e70f5615-c44a-4fc2-b58b-a1c19c3b9f33"}
